TrpzAssociationFailureType.name: TrpzAssociationFailureType
TrpzAssociationFailureType.description: Enumeration of the reasons for an AP to fail a client's 802.11 association

TrpzAuthenticationFailureType.name: TrpzAuthenticationFailureType
TrpzAuthenticationFailureType.description: Enumeration of the reasons for AAA authentication to fail user-glob-mismatch - auth rule/user not found for console login user-does-not-exist - login failed because user not found invalid-password - login failed because of invalid password server-timeout - unable to contact a AAA server signature-failed - incorrect password for mschapv2 local-certificate-error - certificate error all-servers-down - unable to contact any AAA server in the group authentication-type-mismatch - client and switch are using different authentication methods server-rejected - received reject from AAA server fallthru-auth-misconfig - problem with fallthru authentication no-lastresort-auth - problem with last-resort authentication exceeded-max-attempts - local user failed to login within allowed number of attempts resulting in account lockout password-expired - user's password expired

TrpzAuthorizationFailureType.name: TrpzAuthorizationFailureType
TrpzAuthorizationFailureType.description: Enumeration of the reasons for AAA authorization failure

TrpzDot1xFailureType.name: TrpzDot1xFailureType
TrpzDot1xFailureType.description: Enumeration of the dot1x failure reasons. quiet-period occurs when client is denied access for a period of time after a failed connection attempt administrative-kill means that the session was cleared using the 'clear dot1x client' command bad-rsnie means that client sent an invalid IE timeout is when there are excessive retransmissions max-sessions-exceeded means the maximum allowed wired clients has been exceeded on the switch fourway-hs-failure is for failures occuring the 4-way key handshake user-glob-mismatch means the name received in the dot1x identity request does not match any configured userglobs in the system reauth-disabled means that the client is trying to reauthenticate but reauthentication is disabled gkhs-failure means that either there was no response from the client during the GKHS or the response did not have an IE force-unauth-configured means that the client is trying to connect through a port which is configured as force-unauth cert-not-installed means that there is no certificate installed on the switch

TrpzRFDetectDoSType.name: TrpzRFDetectDoSType
TrpzRFDetectDoSType.description: The types of denial of service (DoS) attacks

TrpzClientIpAddrChangeReason.name: TrpzClientIpAddrChangeReason
TrpzClientIpAddrChangeReason.description: Describes the reasons for client IP address changes: client-connected-ipv4: an IPv4 address was assigned on the initial connection of an IPv4 client, or when an IPv6 client activated the IPv4 stack; other: IPv4 address changed after initial connection; dhcp-to-static: erroneous condition where client IPv4 address is changed to a static address while the dhcp-restrict option is enabled; ipv6-global-addr: a new IPv6 global address was assigned to the client.

TrpzBlacklistingCause.name: TrpzBlacklistingCause
TrpzBlacklistingCause.description: Enumeration of reasons for blacklisting a transmitter: bl-configured: administrative action (explicitly added to the Black List), bl-associate-pkt-flood: Association request flood detected, bl-re-associate-pkt-flood: Re-association request flood detected, bl-de-associate-pkt-flood: De-association request flood detected. (The leading 'bl-' stands for 'Black-Listed'; reading it as 'Blocked' would also make sense).

TrpzUserAttributeList.name: TrpzUserAttributeList
TrpzUserAttributeList.description: Display string listing AAA attributes and their values. These strings can be used, for example, in change of authorization notifications. The syntax is: attribute_name1=value1, attribute_name2=value2, ... where attribute_name can be one of the following: vlan-name, in-acl, out-acl, mobility-prof, time-of-day, end-date, sess-timeout, acct-interval, service-type. Example: vlan-name=red, in-acl=in_acl_1

TrpzSessionDisconnectType.name: TrpzSessionDisconnectType
TrpzSessionDisconnectType.description: Enumeration of the sources that can initiate the termination of a session: admin-disconnect: session terminated by administrative action (from console, telnet session, WebView, or RingMaster). dyn-auth-disconnect: session terminated by dynamic authorization client; description will have the IP address of the dynamic authorization client which sent the request.

TrpzConfigSaveInitiatorType.name: TrpzConfigSaveInitiatorType
TrpzConfigSaveInitiatorType.description: Enumeration of the sources that can initiate a configuration save: cli-console: configuration save requested from serial console administrative session. cli-remote: configuration save requested from telnet or ssh administrative session. https: configuration save requested via HTTPS API (RingMaster or WebView). snmp-set: configuration saved as a result of performing a SNMP SET operation.

TrpzMichaelMICFailureCause.name: TrpzMichaelMICFailureCause
TrpzMichaelMICFailureCause.description: Describes the cause/source of Michael MIC Failure detection.

TrpzClientAuthorizationReason.name: TrpzClientAuthorizationReason
TrpzClientAuthorizationReason.description: Enumeration of the reasons for AAA authorization.

TrpzApMgrChangeReason.name: TrpzApMgrChangeReason
TrpzApMgrChangeReason.description: Enumeration of the reasons why AP is switching to its secondary link: failover: AP's primary link failed. load-balancing: AP's primary link is overloaded.

TrpzClientClearedReason.name: TrpzClientClearedReason
TrpzClientClearedReason.description: Enumeration of the reasons for clearing a session: normal: Session was cleared from the switch as the last step in the normal session termination process. backup-failure: The backup switch could not activate a session from a failed MX.

TrpzMobilityDomainResiliencyStatus.name: TrpzMobilityDomainResiliencyStatus
TrpzMobilityDomainResiliencyStatus.description: Enumeration of the current resilient capacity status for a mobility domain: resilient: Every AP in the mobility domain has a secondary backup link. If the primary switch of an AP failed, the AP and its sessions would fail over to its backup link. degraded: Some APs only have a primary link. If the primary switch of an AP without a backup link failed, the AP would reboot and its sessions would be lost.

TrpzClusterFailureReason.name: TrpzClusterFailureReason
TrpzClusterFailureReason.description: Enumeration of the reasons why the AC goes into cluster failure state: validation-error: Cluster configuration rejected due to validation error.

TrpzMultimediaSignalingProtocol.name: TrpzMultimediaSignalingProtocol
TrpzMultimediaSignalingProtocol.description: Enumeration of Multimedia Signaling Protocols: protocols for creating, modifying, terminating sessions. The first signaling protocol supported is: sip = Session Initiation Protocol.

TrpzMultimediaCallFailureReason.name: TrpzMultimediaCallFailureReason
TrpzMultimediaCallFailureReason.description: Enumeration of the reasons why a multimedia call fails.

TrpzMultimediaCallDirection.name: TrpzMultimediaCallDirection
TrpzMultimediaCallDirection.description: Enumeration of the multimedia call direction.

TrpzWsTunnelLimitType.name: TrpzWsTunnelLimitType
TrpzWsTunnelLimitType.description: Enumeration of the type of limit exceeded that caused the AC (wireless switch) to reject a tunnel creation request. The value 'platform-tunnel-limit' (2) corresponds to the maximum tunnel capacity of a switch, which depends on the platform. Some of the available tunnel capacity for each switch is reserved for switch-to-switch tunnels. The remaining tunnel capacity is used for AP-to-switch tunnels. The switch-to-switch tunnel reservations can increase or decrease depending on factors such as: - the current number of members in the mobility domain, - the current number of members in the network domain, - network resiliency status. The value 'ap-ws-tunnel-limit' (3) corresponds to the available number of AP-to-switch tunnels, which depends on the current situation of the switch.

TrpzM2UConvNotPossibleReason.name: TrpzM2UConvNotPossibleReason
TrpzM2UConvNotPossibleReason.description: Enumeration of the reasons why multicast to unicast conversion cannot be performed. max-conv-limit: The number of required conversions is higher than the defined limit.

TrpzRadioBand.name: TrpzRadioBand
TrpzRadioBand.description: Enumeration of the 802.11 radio bands. 802.11 a/n use the 5 GHz band. 802.11 b/g/n use the 2.4 GHz band.

TrpzAutoTuneFailureReason.name: TrpzAutoTuneFailureReason
TrpzAutoTuneFailureReason.description: Enumeration of the reasons why an auto-tune operation failed: ap-conn-lost: The connection with an AP involved in the auto-tune process was lost. ws-conn-lost: The connection with a wireless switch involved in the auto-tune process was lost.

TrpzClientDeviceProfileChangeReason.name: TrpzClientDeviceProfileChangeReason
TrpzClientDeviceProfileChangeReason.description: Enumeration of the reasons for device profile changes. aaa-policy: The device profile has changed due to an AAA policy, after authentication. device-type-changed: The device type has changed.

trpzDeviceId.name: trpzDeviceId
trpzDeviceId.description: Enumeration of devices as indicated in registration MIB. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMobilityDomainIp.name: trpzMobilityDomainIp
trpzMobilityDomainIp.description: IP address of the other switch which the send switch is reporting on. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzAPMACAddress.name: trpzAPMACAddress
trpzAPMACAddress.description: MAC address of the AP of interest. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientMACAddress.name: trpzClientMACAddress
trpzClientMACAddress.description: MAC address of the client of interest. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr.name: trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr
trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr.description: Describes the transmitter's MAC address. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzPortNum.name: trpzPortNum
trpzPortNum.description: Port number on the AC which reported this rogue during a detection sweep. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzAPRadioNum.name: trpzAPRadioNum
trpzAPRadioNum.description: Radio number of the AP which reported this rogue during a detection sweep. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRadioRssi.name: trpzRadioRssi
trpzRadioRssi.description: The received signal strength as measured by the AP radio which reported this rogue during a detection sweep. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible. Not used by any notification.

trpzRadioBSSID.name: trpzRadioBSSID
trpzRadioBSSID.description: The basic service set identifier of the rogue from the beacon frame reported by the AP during a detection sweep. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzUserName.name: trpzUserName
trpzUserName.description: The client user name as learned from the AAA process. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientAuthServerIp.name: trpzClientAuthServerIp
trpzClientAuthServerIp.description: The client authentication server ip address. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientSessionState.name: trpzClientSessionState
trpzClientSessionState.description: The state for a client session. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzDAPNum.name: trpzDAPNum
trpzDAPNum.description: The DAP number on the wireless switch. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientIp.name: trpzClientIp
trpzClientIp.description: The client ip address. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientSessionId.name: trpzClientSessionId
trpzClientSessionId.description: The unique global id for a client session. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientAuthenProtocolType.name: trpzClientAuthenProtocolType
trpzClientAuthenProtocolType.description: The authentication protocol for a client. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientVLANName.name: trpzClientVLANName
trpzClientVLANName.description: The vlan name a client is on. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientSessionStartTime.name: trpzClientSessionStartTime
trpzClientSessionStartTime.description: The start time of a client session, relative to the sysUptime. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible. Obsolete. Do not use it because it's not vital information and often *cannot* be implemented to match the declared semantics: a client session might have been created on another wireless switch, *before* the current switch booted (the local zero of sysUptime).

trpzClientFailureCause.name: trpzClientFailureCause
trpzClientFailureCause.description: Display string for possible failure cause for a client session. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientRoamedFromPortNum.name: trpzClientRoamedFromPortNum
trpzClientRoamedFromPortNum.description: The port number on the AC a client has roamed from. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible. Obsoleted by 'trpzClientRoamedFromPhysPortNum'.

trpzClientRoamedFromRadioNum.name: trpzClientRoamedFromRadioNum
trpzClientRoamedFromRadioNum.description: The radio number of the AP the client is roamed from. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible. Obsoleted by 'trpzClientRoamedFromRadioIndex'.

trpzClientRoamedFromDAPNum.name: trpzClientRoamedFromDAPNum
trpzClientRoamedFromDAPNum.description: The DAP number on the AC which reported this rogue during roam. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible. Obsoleted by 'trpzClientRoamedFromApNum'.

trpzUserParams.name: trpzUserParams
trpzUserParams.description: A display string of User Parameters for client user authorization attributes learned through AAA and/or used by the system. Note that the syntax will be (name=value, name=value,..) for the parsing purpose. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientLocationPolicyIndex.name: trpzClientLocationPolicyIndex
trpzClientLocationPolicyIndex.description: Index of the Location Policy rule applied to a user. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientAssociationFailureCause.name: trpzClientAssociationFailureCause
trpzClientAssociationFailureCause.description: The client association failure cause. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientAuthenticationFailureCause.name: trpzClientAuthenticationFailureCause
trpzClientAuthenticationFailureCause.description: The client authentication failure cause. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientAuthorizationFailureCause.name: trpzClientAuthorizationFailureCause
trpzClientAuthorizationFailureCause.description: The client authorization failure cause. Note that if it is the user-param, we would additionally expect the failure cause description to list the user attribute value that caused the failure. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientFailureCauseDescription.name: trpzClientFailureCauseDescription
trpzClientFailureCauseDescription.description: Display string for describing the client failure cause. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientRoamedFromWsIp.name: trpzClientRoamedFromWsIp
trpzClientRoamedFromWsIp.description: The system IP address of the AC (wireless switch) a client roamed from. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientRoamedFromAccessType.name: trpzClientRoamedFromAccessType
trpzClientRoamedFromAccessType.description: The client access type (ap, dap, wired) that a client roamed from. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible. Obsoleted by 'trpzClientRoamedFromAccessMode'.

trpzClientAccessType.name: trpzClientAccessType
trpzClientAccessType.description: The client access type (ap, dap, wired). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible. For new traps, use trpzClientAccessMode instead of this object.

trpzRadioMACAddress.name: trpzRadioMACAddress
trpzRadioMACAddress.description: AP Radio MAC address. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRadioPowerChangeReason.name: trpzRadioPowerChangeReason
trpzRadioPowerChangeReason.description: The type of event that caused an AP radio power change; occurs due to auto-tune operation. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzNewChannelNum.name: trpzNewChannelNum
trpzNewChannelNum.description: New channel number of the AP radio used after an auto tune event. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzOldChannelNum.name: trpzOldChannelNum
trpzOldChannelNum.description: Old channel number of the AP radio used before an auto tune event. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzChannelChangeReason.name: trpzChannelChangeReason
trpzChannelChangeReason.description: The type of event that caused an AP radio channel change; occurs due to auto-tune operation. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo.name: trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo
trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo.description: The RF Detection Listener list info including a list of (listener mac, rssi, channel, ssid, time). There will be a maximum of 6 entries in the list. Formats: MAC: 18 bytes: %2.2X:%2.2X:%2.2X:%2.2X:%2.2X:%2.2X RSSI: 10 bytes: %10d CHANNEL: 3 bytes: %3d SSID: 32 bytes: %s TIME: 26 bytes: %s Maximum size per entry is 89+4+2 = 95 bytes. Maximum size of the string is 6*95= 571 bytes (include NULL). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRadioSSID.name: trpzRadioSSID
trpzRadioSSID.description: The radio SSID string This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzNewPowerLevel.name: trpzNewPowerLevel
trpzNewPowerLevel.description: New power level of the AP radio used after an auto tune event. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzOldPowerLevel.name: trpzOldPowerLevel
trpzOldPowerLevel.description: Old power level of the AP radio used before an auto tune event. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRadioPowerChangeDescription.name: trpzRadioPowerChangeDescription
trpzRadioPowerChangeDescription.description: The radio power change description. In the case of reason being dup-pkts-threshold-exceed(1), and retransmit-threshold-exceed(2), clientMacAddress will be included in the description. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzCounterMeasurePerformerListInfo.name: trpzCounterMeasurePerformerListInfo
trpzCounterMeasurePerformerListInfo.description: A list of information for APs performing Counter Measures including a list of performer mac addresses. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible. Not used by any notification.

trpzClientDot1xState.name: trpzClientDot1xState
trpzClientDot1xState.description: The state for a client 802.1X. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientDot1xFailureCause.name: trpzClientDot1xFailureCause
trpzClientDot1xFailureCause.description: The client 802.1X failure cause. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzAPAccessType.name: trpzAPAccessType
trpzAPAccessType.description: The access point access type (ap, dap,). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible. Not used by any notification.

trpzUserAccessType.name: trpzUserAccessType
trpzUserAccessType.description: The user access type (MAC, WEB, DOT1X, LAST-RESORT). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientSessionElapsedTime.name: trpzClientSessionElapsedTime
trpzClientSessionElapsedTime.description: The elapsed time for a client session. Obsoleted because session time is usually reported in seconds. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzLocalId.name: trpzLocalId
trpzLocalId.description: Local Id for the session. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFDetectDoSType.name: trpzRFDetectDoSType
trpzRFDetectDoSType.description: The type of denial of service (DoS) attack. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzSourceWsIp.name: trpzSourceWsIp
trpzSourceWsIp.description: IP address of another AC (wireless switch). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientVLANid.name: trpzClientVLANid
trpzClientVLANid.description: VLAN ID used by client traffic. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientVLANtag.name: trpzClientVLANtag
trpzClientVLANtag.description: VLAN tag used by client traffic. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzDeviceModel.name: trpzDeviceModel
trpzDeviceModel.description: The model of a device in printable US-ASCII. If unknown (or not available), then the value is a zero length string. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzDeviceSerNum.name: trpzDeviceSerNum
trpzDeviceSerNum.description: The serial number of an AP in printable US-ASCII. If unknown (or not available), then the value is a zero length string. Should NOT be used to identify other devices, for example an AC (wireless switch). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRsaPubKeyFingerPrint.name: trpzRsaPubKeyFingerPrint
trpzRsaPubKeyFingerPrint.description: The hash of the RSA public key (of a key pair) in binary form that uniquely identifies the public key of an AP. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzDAPconnectWarningType.name: trpzDAPconnectWarningType
trpzDAPconnectWarningType.description: The type of DAP connect warning. The values are: not-configured-fingerprint-connect(1)...a DAP, which has an RSA keypair but did not have its fingerprint configured on the AC, has connected to the AC when 'dap security' set to 'OPTIONAL' secure-handshake-failure(2).............a DAP tried to connect to the AC with security, but the handshake failed not-configured-fingerprint-required(3)..a DAP tried to connect to the AC with security, but 'dap security' set to 'REQUIRED', and no fingerprint was configured for the DAP fingerprint-mismatch(4).................a DAP tried to connect to the AC with security and its fingerprint was configured, but the fingerprint did not match the computed one This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientMACAddress2.name: trpzClientMACAddress2
trpzClientMACAddress2.description: MAC address of the second client of interest. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzApAttachType.name: trpzApAttachType
trpzApAttachType.description: How the AP is attached to the AC (directly or via L2/L3 network). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzApPortOrDapNum.name: trpzApPortOrDapNum
trpzApPortOrDapNum.description: The Port Number if the AP is directly attached, or the CLI-assigned DAP Number if attached via L2/L3 network. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible. Obsoleted by trpzApNum. (In 6.0, direct- and network-attached APs were unified.)

trpzApName.name: trpzApName
trpzApName.description: The name of the AP, as assigned in AC's CLI; defaults to AP<Number> (examples: 'AP01', 'AP22', 'AP333', 'AP4444'); could have been changed from CLI to a meaningful name, for example the location of the AP (example: 'MeetingRoom73'). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzApTransition.name: trpzApTransition
trpzApTransition.description: AP state Transition, as seen by the AC. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzApFailDetail.name: trpzApFailDetail
trpzApFailDetail.description: Detailed failure code for some of the transitions specified in 'trpzApTransition' object. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRadioType.name: trpzRadioType
trpzRadioType.description: Indicates the AP Radio Type, as seen by AC. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRadioConfigState.name: trpzRadioConfigState
trpzRadioConfigState.description: Indicates the Radio State, as seen by the AC. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzApConnectSecurityType.name: trpzApConnectSecurityType
trpzApConnectSecurityType.description: Indicates the security level of the connection between AP and AC. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzApServiceAvailability.name: trpzApServiceAvailability
trpzApServiceAvailability.description: Indicates the level of wireless service availability. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzApWasOperational.name: trpzApWasOperational
trpzApWasOperational.description: Indicates whether the AP was operational before a transition occurred. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientTimeSinceLastRoam.name: trpzClientTimeSinceLastRoam
trpzClientTimeSinceLastRoam.description: The time in seconds since the most recent roam of a given client. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientIpAddrChangeReason.name: trpzClientIpAddrChangeReason
trpzClientIpAddrChangeReason.description: Indicates the reason why client IP address changed. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFDetectRogueAPMacAddr.name: trpzRFDetectRogueAPMacAddr
trpzRFDetectRogueAPMacAddr.description: Describes the MAC address of the Rogue AP the transmitter is connected to. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzBlacklistingRemainingTime.name: trpzBlacklistingRemainingTime
trpzBlacklistingRemainingTime.description: The time in seconds remaining until a given transmitter could be removed from the Black List. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzBlacklistingCause.name: trpzBlacklistingCause
trpzBlacklistingCause.description: Indicates the reason why a given transmitter is blacklisted. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzNumLicensedActiveAPs.name: trpzNumLicensedActiveAPs
trpzNumLicensedActiveAPs.description: Indicates the maximum (licensed) number of active APs for this AC. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientDynAuthorClientIp.name: trpzClientDynAuthorClientIp
trpzClientDynAuthorClientIp.description: The dynamic authorization client IP address which caused the change of authorization. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzChangedUserParamOldValues.name: trpzChangedUserParamOldValues
trpzChangedUserParamOldValues.description: A display string listing the changed AAA attributes and their values, before the change of authorization was executed. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzChangedUserParamNewValues.name: trpzChangedUserParamNewValues
trpzChangedUserParamNewValues.description: A display string listing the changed AAA attributes and their values, after the change of authorization was executed. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientDisconnectSource.name: trpzClientDisconnectSource
trpzClientDisconnectSource.description: The external source that initiated the termination of a session. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientDisconnectDescription.name: trpzClientDisconnectDescription
trpzClientDisconnectDescription.description: Display string for providing available information related to the external source that initiated a session termination. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMobilityDomainSecondarySeedIp.name: trpzMobilityDomainSecondarySeedIp
trpzMobilityDomainSecondarySeedIp.description: The secondary seed IP address to which the Mobility Domain has failed over. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMobilityDomainPrimarySeedIp.name: trpzMobilityDomainPrimarySeedIp
trpzMobilityDomainPrimarySeedIp.description: The primary seed IP address to which the Mobility Domain has failed back. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFDetectClassificationReason.name: trpzRFDetectClassificationReason
trpzRFDetectClassificationReason.description: Indicates the reason why a RF device is classified the way it is. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzConfigSaveFileName.name: trpzConfigSaveFileName
trpzConfigSaveFileName.description: Display string listing the name of the file to which the running configuration was saved. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzConfigSaveInitiatorType.name: trpzConfigSaveInitiatorType
trpzConfigSaveInitiatorType.description: Indicates the source that initiated a configuration save. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzConfigSaveInitiatorIp.name: trpzConfigSaveInitiatorIp
trpzConfigSaveInitiatorIp.description: The IP address of the source that initiated a configuration save. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzConfigSaveInitiatorDetails.name: trpzConfigSaveInitiatorDetails
trpzConfigSaveInitiatorDetails.description: Display string listing additional information regarding the source that initiated a configuration save, when available. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzConfigSaveGeneration.name: trpzConfigSaveGeneration
trpzConfigSaveGeneration.description: Indicates the number of configuration changes since the last system boot. The generation count is used to track the number of times the running configuration has been changed due to administrative actions (set/clear), SNMP requests (SET), XML requests (e.g. RingMaster). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzApNum.name: trpzApNum
trpzApNum.description: The administratively assigned AP Number, unique on same AC (switch), regardless of how APs are attached to the AC. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible. Obsoletes trpzApPortOrDapNum. For clarity, use this object to identify an AP since in 6.0 directly attached APs and DAPs were unified.

trpzRadioMode.name: trpzRadioMode
trpzRadioMode.description: Indicates the administratively controlled Radio Mode (enabled/disabled/sentry). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMichaelMICFailureCause.name: trpzMichaelMICFailureCause
trpzMichaelMICFailureCause.description: Indicates the Michael MIC Failure cause / who detected it. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientAccessMode.name: trpzClientAccessMode
trpzClientAccessMode.description: The client access mode (ap, wired). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible. Intended to replace trpzClientAccessType. (In 6.0, direct- and network-attached APs were unified.)

trpzClientAuthorizationReason.name: trpzClientAuthorizationReason
trpzClientAuthorizationReason.description: Indicates the reason why client performed AAA authorization. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzPhysPortNum.name: trpzPhysPortNum
trpzPhysPortNum.description: Physical Port Number on the AC. Zero means the port is unknown or not applicable (for example, when trpzClientAccessMode = 'ap'). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzApMgrOldIp.name: trpzApMgrOldIp
trpzApMgrOldIp.description: The IP address of the AP's former primary manager switch. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzApMgrNewIp.name: trpzApMgrNewIp
trpzApMgrNewIp.description: The IP address of the AP's new primary manager switch. This address was formerly the AP's secondary backup link. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzApMgrChangeReason.name: trpzApMgrChangeReason
trpzApMgrChangeReason.description: Indicates the reason why the AP's primary manager changed. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientClearedReason.name: trpzClientClearedReason
trpzClientClearedReason.description: Indicates the reason why client was cleared. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMobilityDomainResiliencyStatus.name: trpzMobilityDomainResiliencyStatus
trpzMobilityDomainResiliencyStatus.description: Indicates the current resilient capacity status for a mobility domain. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientSessionElapsedSeconds.name: trpzClientSessionElapsedSeconds
trpzClientSessionElapsedSeconds.description: Indicates the time in seconds elapsed since the start of the Client Session. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRadioChannelWidth.name: trpzRadioChannelWidth
trpzRadioChannelWidth.description: Indicates the administratively controlled Channel Width (20MHz/40MHz). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRadioMimoState.name: trpzRadioMimoState
trpzRadioMimoState.description: Indicates the Radio MIMO State, as seen by the AC (1x1/2x3/3x3). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientRadioType.name: trpzClientRadioType
trpzClientRadioType.description: Indicates the Client Radio Type, as detected by an attached AP and reported to the AC. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFDetectXmtrRadioType.name: trpzRFDetectXmtrRadioType
trpzRFDetectXmtrRadioType.description: Indicates the Radio Type of the Transmitter, as detected by an attached AP and reported to the AC. The Transmitter may be a wireless client or an AP. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFDetectXmtrCryptoType.name: trpzRFDetectXmtrCryptoType
trpzRFDetectXmtrCryptoType.description: Indicates the Crypto Type used by the Transmitter, as detected by an attached AP and reported to the AC. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClusterFailureReason.name: trpzClusterFailureReason
trpzClusterFailureReason.description: Indicates the reason why cluster configuration failed to apply. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClusterFailureDescription.name: trpzClusterFailureDescription
trpzClusterFailureDescription.description: Display string for describing the cluster configuration failure cause. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMultimediaCommunicationServerID.name: trpzMultimediaCommunicationServerID
trpzMultimediaCommunicationServerID.description: The multimedia communication server ID. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMultimediaLocalStationIp.name: trpzMultimediaLocalStationIp
trpzMultimediaLocalStationIp.description: The local multimedia station IP address. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMultimediaLocalStationPort.name: trpzMultimediaLocalStationPort
trpzMultimediaLocalStationPort.description: The local multimedia station UDP port. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMultimediaLocalStationEndpointID.name: trpzMultimediaLocalStationEndpointID
trpzMultimediaLocalStationEndpointID.description: The local multimedia station endpoint ID. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMultimediaRemoteStationIp.name: trpzMultimediaRemoteStationIp
trpzMultimediaRemoteStationIp.description: The remote multimedia station IP address. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMultimediaRemoteStationPort.name: trpzMultimediaRemoteStationPort
trpzMultimediaRemoteStationPort.description: The remote multimedia station UDP port. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMultimediaRemoteStationEndpointID.name: trpzMultimediaRemoteStationEndpointID
trpzMultimediaRemoteStationEndpointID.description: The remote multimedia station endpoint ID. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMultimediaSignalingProtocol.name: trpzMultimediaSignalingProtocol
trpzMultimediaSignalingProtocol.description: The multimedia signaling protocol that was used for initiating this call (session). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMultimediaCallBandwidthAndCodec.name: trpzMultimediaCallBandwidthAndCodec
trpzMultimediaCallBandwidthAndCodec.description: Display string providing information about the multimedia call codec and bandwidth. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMultimediaCallDataRate.name: trpzMultimediaCallDataRate
trpzMultimediaCallDataRate.description: The data rate, in Kbps. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMultimediaCallRssi.name: trpzMultimediaCallRssi
trpzMultimediaCallRssi.description: The client RSSI (Received Signal Strength Indicator), in decibels referred to 1 milliwatt (dBm). A higher value indicates a stronger signal. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMultimediaCallFailureReason.name: trpzMultimediaCallFailureReason
trpzMultimediaCallFailureReason.description: Indicates the reason why the multimedia call has failed. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzMultimediaCallDirection.name: trpzMultimediaCallDirection
trpzMultimediaCallDirection.description: Indicates the multimedia call direction (incoming/outgoing). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzApTunnelLimit.name: trpzApTunnelLimit
trpzApTunnelLimit.description: Indicates the maximum number of tunnels supported for an AP. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzWsTunnelLimit.name: trpzWsTunnelLimit
trpzWsTunnelLimit.description: Indicates the maximum number of tunnels supported for an AC (wireless switch). This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzWsTunnelLimitType.name: trpzWsTunnelLimitType
trpzWsTunnelLimitType.description: Indicates the type of limit exceeded that caused the AC (wireless switch) to reject a tunnel creation request. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFNoiseSourceID.name: trpzRFNoiseSourceID
trpzRFNoiseSourceID.description: RF Noise Source ID. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFNoiseSourceType.name: trpzRFNoiseSourceType
trpzRFNoiseSourceType.description: RF Noise Source Type. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFNoiseChannel.name: trpzRFNoiseChannel
trpzRFNoiseChannel.description: Channel number. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFNoiseRssi.name: trpzRFNoiseRssi
trpzRFNoiseRssi.description: The noise RSSI (Received Signal Strength Indicator), in decibels referred to 1 milliwatt (dBm). A higher value indicates stronger noise. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFNoiseDutyCycle.name: trpzRFNoiseDutyCycle
trpzRFNoiseDutyCycle.description: Estimated Duty Cycle: fraction of time that a noise source is transmitting. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFNoiseChannelInterferenceMeasure.name: trpzRFNoiseChannelInterferenceMeasure
trpzRFNoiseChannelInterferenceMeasure.description: Severity of channel interference attributed to a noise source. A higher value indicates more severe interference. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRFNoiseAge.name: trpzRFNoiseAge
trpzRFNoiseAge.description: Age of noise in seconds. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzM2UMulticastAddrType.name: trpzM2UMulticastAddrType
trpzM2UMulticastAddrType.description: The address type of 'trpzM2UMulticastAddr'. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzM2UMulticastAddr.name: trpzM2UMulticastAddr
trpzM2UMulticastAddr.description: The multicast address for which conversion to unicast is performed. The type of this address is specified in 'trpzM2UMulticastAddrType'. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzM2UConvNotPossibleReason.name: trpzM2UConvNotPossibleReason
trpzM2UConvNotPossibleReason.description: Indicates the reason why multicast to unicast conversion cannot be performed on an AP with this feature enabled. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRadioBand.name: trpzRadioBand
trpzRadioBand.description: Indicates the radio band used in an auto-tune operation. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzRadiosTunedCount.name: trpzRadiosTunedCount
trpzRadiosTunedCount.description: Indicates how many radios had their operational characteristics changed as a result of an auto-tune process. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzAutoTuneFailureReason.name: trpzAutoTuneFailureReason
trpzAutoTuneFailureReason.description: Indicates the reason why an auto-tune operation failed to complete. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientAuthServerAddrType.name: trpzClientAuthServerAddrType
trpzClientAuthServerAddrType.description: The address type of 'trpzClientAuthServerAddr'. Only the value 'ipv4(1)' is reported as of release 8.0. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientAuthServerAddr.name: trpzClientAuthServerAddr
trpzClientAuthServerAddr.description: The Internet address of the client authentication server. The type of this address is specified in 'trpzClientAuthServerAddrType'. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientRoamedFromWsAddrType.name: trpzClientRoamedFromWsAddrType
trpzClientRoamedFromWsAddrType.description: The address type of 'trpzClientRoamedFromWsAddr'. Only the value 'ipv4(1)' is reported as of release 8.0. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientRoamedFromWsAddr.name: trpzClientRoamedFromWsAddr
trpzClientRoamedFromWsAddr.description: The system IP address of the AC (wireless switch) a client roamed from. The type of this address is specified in 'trpzClientRoamedFromWsAddrType'. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientDynAuthorClientAddrType.name: trpzClientDynAuthorClientAddrType
trpzClientDynAuthorClientAddrType.description: The address type of 'trpzClientDynAuthorClientAddr'. Only the value 'ipv4(1)' is reported as of release 8.0. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientDynAuthorClientAddr.name: trpzClientDynAuthorClientAddr
trpzClientDynAuthorClientAddr.description: The dynamic authorization client IP address which caused the change of authorization. The type of this address is specified in 'trpzClientDynAuthorClientAddrType'. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientIpAddrType.name: trpzClientIpAddrType
trpzClientIpAddrType.description: The address type of 'trpzClientIpAddr'. Only the values 'ipv4(1)' and 'ipv6(2)' are reported. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientIpAddr.name: trpzClientIpAddr
trpzClientIpAddr.description: Indicates an IP address of the client. The type of this address is specified in 'trpzClientIpAddrType'. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientIPv4Addr.name: trpzClientIPv4Addr
trpzClientIPv4Addr.description: The IPv4 address of the client. If the client does not use the IPv4 stack, or its IPv4 address has not yet been detected, then all octets will have the value 0. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientIPv6LinkLocalAddr.name: trpzClientIPv6LinkLocalAddr
trpzClientIPv6LinkLocalAddr.description: The IPv6 link-local address of the client. If the client does not use the IPv6 stack, or its IPv6 link-local address has not yet been detected, then all octets will have the value 0. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzApRadioIndex.name: trpzApRadioIndex
trpzApRadioIndex.description: AP Radio index. Intended to replace 'trpzAPRadioNum'. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientRoamedFromAccessMode.name: trpzClientRoamedFromAccessMode
trpzClientRoamedFromAccessMode.description: The client access mode (ap, wired) that a client roamed from. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible. Obsoletes 'trpzClientRoamedFromAccessType'. (In 6.0, direct- and network-attached APs were unified.)

trpzClientRoamedFromApNum.name: trpzClientRoamedFromApNum
trpzClientRoamedFromApNum.description: The number of the AP the client roamed from. Obsoletes 'trpzClientRoamedFromDAPNum'. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientRoamedFromRadioIndex.name: trpzClientRoamedFromRadioIndex
trpzClientRoamedFromRadioIndex.description: The index of the AP Radio the client roamed from. Obsoletes 'trpzClientRoamedFromRadioNum'. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientRoamedFromPhysPortNum.name: trpzClientRoamedFromPhysPortNum
trpzClientRoamedFromPhysPortNum.description: Identifies the physical port on the AC used by the wired-auth client, before roam. Zero means the port is unknown or not applicable (for example, when trpzClientRoamedFromAccessMode = 'ap'). Obsoletes 'trpzClientRoamedFromPortNum'. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientDeviceType.name: trpzClientDeviceType
trpzClientDeviceType.description: The type of the client device. Is a zero length string if unknown. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientDeviceTypeOld.name: trpzClientDeviceTypeOld
trpzClientDeviceTypeOld.description: The type of the client device, before change. Is a zero length string if unknown. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientDeviceGroup.name: trpzClientDeviceGroup
trpzClientDeviceGroup.description: The group that the detected client device type belongs to. Is a zero length string if the device type is unknown. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientDeviceProfileName.name: trpzClientDeviceProfileName
trpzClientDeviceProfileName.description: The name of the device profile associated with the detected client device. A device profile is a collection of policies that apply to one or more types of client devices. Is a zero length string in 'detect-only' mode or if not set. In 'detect-only' mode policy enforcement is disabled. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientDeviceProfileNameOld.name: trpzClientDeviceProfileNameOld
trpzClientDeviceProfileNameOld.description: The name of the device profile associated with the detected client device, before change. A device profile is a collection of policies that apply to one or more types of client devices. Is a zero length string in 'detect-only' mode or if not set. In 'detect-only' mode policy enforcement is disabled. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzClientDeviceProfileChangeReason.name: trpzClientDeviceProfileChangeReason
trpzClientDeviceProfileChangeReason.description: The reason why the device profile changed. This object is used within notifications and is not accessible.

trpzDeviceFailTrap.name: trpzDeviceFailTrap
trpzDeviceFailTrap.description: The device has a failure indication

trpzPoEFailTrap.name: trpzPoEFailTrap
trpzPoEFailTrap.description: PoE has failed on the indicated port

trpzApTimeoutTrap.name: trpzApTimeoutTrap
trpzApTimeoutTrap.description: The AP entering the AC at port trpzPortNum with MAC trpzRadioMacAddress and of the access type (ap or dap) has not responded. Replaced by trpzApNonOperStatusTrap2, with trpzApTransition = 'timeout'.

trpzAPBootTrap.name: trpzAPBootTrap
trpzAPBootTrap.description: The AP entering the AC at port trpzPortNum with MAC trpzRadioMacAddress and of the access type (ap or dap) has booted. Replaced by trpzApNonOperStatusTrap2, with trpzApTransition = 'bootSuccess'.

trpzMobilityDomainJoinTrap.name: trpzMobilityDomainJoinTrap
trpzMobilityDomainJoinTrap.description: The mobility domain member has received an UP notice from the remote address.

trpzMobilityDomainTimeoutTrap.name: trpzMobilityDomainTimeoutTrap
trpzMobilityDomainTimeoutTrap.description: The mobility domain member has declared the remote address to be DOWN.

trpzMpMichaelMICFailure.name: trpzMpMichaelMICFailure
trpzMpMichaelMICFailure.description: Two Michael MIC failures were seen within 60 seconds of each other. Obsoleted by trpzMichaelMICFailure.

trpzRFDetectRogueAPTrap.name: trpzRFDetectRogueAPTrap
trpzRFDetectRogueAPTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection finds a rogue AP. XmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. ListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. Obsoleted by trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap2.

trpzRFDetectAdhocUserTrap.name: trpzRFDetectAdhocUserTrap
trpzRFDetectAdhocUserTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection sweep finds a ad-hoc user. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the MAC address of the ad-hoc user. trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information.

trpzRFDetectRogueDisappearTrap.name: trpzRFDetectRogueDisappearTrap
trpzRFDetectRogueDisappearTrap.description: This trap is sent when a rogue has disappeared. Obsoleted by trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceDisappearTrap.

trpzClientAuthenticationFailureTrap.name: trpzClientAuthenticationFailureTrap
trpzClientAuthenticationFailureTrap.description: This trap is sent if a client authentication fails.

trpzClientAuthorizationFailureTrap.name: trpzClientAuthorizationFailureTrap
trpzClientAuthorizationFailureTrap.description: This trap is sent if a client authorization fails.

trpzClientAssociationFailureTrap.name: trpzClientAssociationFailureTrap
trpzClientAssociationFailureTrap.description: This trap is sent if a client association fails.

trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap.name: trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap
trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap.description: This trap is sent when a client authorizes. Obsoleted by trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap5.

trpzClientDeAssociationTrap.name: trpzClientDeAssociationTrap
trpzClientDeAssociationTrap.description: This trap is sent if a client de-association occurred. Obsoleted by trpzClientDeAssociationTrap2.

trpzClientRoamingTrap.name: trpzClientRoamingTrap
trpzClientRoamingTrap.description: This trap is sent if a client roams from one location to another. Obsoleted by trpzClientRoamingTrap2.

trpzAutoTuneRadioPowerChangeTrap.name: trpzAutoTuneRadioPowerChangeTrap
trpzAutoTuneRadioPowerChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent if a radio's power level has changed based on auto-tune.

trpzAutoTuneRadioChannelChangeTrap.name: trpzAutoTuneRadioChannelChangeTrap
trpzAutoTuneRadioChannelChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent if a radio's channel has changed based on auto-tune.

trpzCounterMeasureStartTrap.name: trpzCounterMeasureStartTrap
trpzCounterMeasureStartTrap.description: This trap is sent when counter measures are started against a rogue. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the mac address of the rogue we are doing counter measures against. trpzRadioMACAddress identifies the radio performing the countermeasures.

trpzCounterMeasureStopTrap.name: trpzCounterMeasureStopTrap
trpzCounterMeasureStopTrap.description: This trap is sent when counter measures are stopped against a rogue. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the mac address of the rogue we were doing counter measures against. trpzRadioMACAddress identifies the radio performing the countermeasures.

trpzClientDot1xFailureTrap.name: trpzClientDot1xFailureTrap
trpzClientDot1xFailureTrap.description: This trap is sent if a client failed 802.1X.

trpzClientClearedTrap.name: trpzClientClearedTrap
trpzClientClearedTrap.description: This trap is sent when a client session is cleared. Obsoleted by trpzClientClearedTrap3.

trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap2.name: trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap2
trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap2.description: This trap is sent when a client authorizes. Obsoleted by trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap5.

trpzRFDetectSpoofedMacAPTrap.name: trpzRFDetectSpoofedMacAPTrap
trpzRFDetectSpoofedMacAPTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection finds an AP using the MAC of the listener. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. Obsoleted by trpzRFDetectDoSTrap and trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap2. One of the two traps will be sent depending on the type of AP MAC spoofing detected.

trpzRFDetectSpoofedSsidAPTrap.name: trpzRFDetectSpoofedSsidAPTrap
trpzRFDetectSpoofedSsidAPTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection finds an AP using the SSID of the listener, and the AP is not in the mobility domain. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. Obsoleted by trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap2 and trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceTrap2. One of the two traps will be sent, depending on RF detection classification rules.

trpzRFDetectDoSTrap.name: trpzRFDetectDoSTrap
trpzRFDetectDoSTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection finds a denial of service (DoS) occurring. trpzRFDetectDoSType specifies the type of DoS. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information.

trpzRFDetectClientViaRogueWiredAPTrap.name: trpzRFDetectClientViaRogueWiredAPTrap
trpzRFDetectClientViaRogueWiredAPTrap.description: This trap is sent when a client is detected that connected via a rogue AP that is attached to a wired port. trpzSourceWsIp is the IP address of the AC (switch) with the wired port. trpzPortNum is the port on the AC. trpzClientVLANid is the VLAN ID of the client's traffic. trpzClientVLANtag is the VLAN tag of the client's traffic. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the MAC address of the client. trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. Obsoleted by trpzRFDetectClientViaRogueWiredAPTrap3.

trpzRFDetectInterferingRogueAPTrap.name: trpzRFDetectInterferingRogueAPTrap
trpzRFDetectInterferingRogueAPTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection finds an interfering rogue AP. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. Obsoleted by trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceTrap2.

trpzRFDetectInterferingRogueDisappearTra.name: trpzRFDetectInterferingRogueDisappearTrap
trpzRFDetectInterferingRogueDisappearTra.description: This trap is sent when an interfering rogue has disappeared. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. Obsoleted by trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceDisappearTrap.

trpzRFDetectUnAuthorizedSsidTrap.name: trpzRFDetectUnAuthorizedSsidTrap
trpzRFDetectUnAuthorizedSsidTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection finds use of an unauthorized SSID. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. Obsoleted by trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap2 and trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceTrap2. One of the two traps will be sent if the device having an unauthorized SSID is classified as rogue or suspect because of this.

trpzRFDetectUnAuthorizedOuiTrap.name: trpzRFDetectUnAuthorizedOuiTrap
trpzRFDetectUnAuthorizedOuiTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection finds use of an unauthorized OUI. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. Obsoleted by trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap2 and trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceTrap2. One of the two traps will be sent if the device having an unauthorized OUI is classified as rogue or suspect because of this.

trpzRFDetectUnAuthorizedAPTrap.name: trpzRFDetectUnAuthorizedAPTrap
trpzRFDetectUnAuthorizedAPTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection finds operation of an unauthorized AP. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. Obsoleted by trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap2.

trpzDAPConnectWarningTrap.name: trpzDAPConnectWarningTrap
trpzDAPConnectWarningTrap.description: A DAP, tried to connect to the AC. trpzDeviceModel provides the model of the DAP. trpzDeviceSerNum provides the serial number of the DAP. trpzRsaPubKeyFingerPrint provides the computed fingerprint of the DAP. trpzDAPconnectWarningType provides the type of connect warning. Replaced by trpzApNonOperStatusTrap2, with trpzApTransition = 'connectFail'.

trpzRFDetectDoSPortTrap.name: trpzRFDetectDoSPortTrap
trpzRFDetectDoSPortTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection finds a denial of service (DoS) occurring. This has port and AP info instead of 'Listener info'. trpzRFDetectDoSType specifies the type of DoS. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. trpzClientAccessType specifies whether wired, AP, or DAP. trpzPortNum (for wired or AP), the port that is used. trpzDAPNum (for a DAP), the ID of the DAP.

trpzMpMichaelMICFailure2.name: trpzMpMichaelMICFailure2
trpzMpMichaelMICFailure2.description: Two Michael MIC failures were seen within 60 seconds of each other. Object trpzClientMACAddress is the source of the first failure, and object trpzClientMACAddress2 source of the second failure. Obsoleted by trpzMichaelMICFailure.

trpzApNonOperStatusTrap.name: trpzApNonOperStatusTrap
trpzApNonOperStatusTrap.description: This trap is sent when the AP changes state and the new one is a non-operational state. Obsoleted by trpzApNonOperStatusTrap2.

trpzApOperRadioStatusTrap.name: trpzApOperRadioStatusTrap
trpzApOperRadioStatusTrap.description: This trap is sent when the Radio changes state. It also contains aggregate information about the AP in operational state - security level and service availability. Obsoleted by trpzApOperRadioStatusTrap3.

trpzClientIpAddrChangeTrap.name: trpzClientIpAddrChangeTrap
trpzClientIpAddrChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent when a client's IP address changes. The most likely case for this is when the client first connects to the network. Obsoleted by trpzClientIpAddrChangeTrap2.

trpzClientAssociationSuccessTrap.name: trpzClientAssociationSuccessTrap
trpzClientAssociationSuccessTrap.description: This trap is sent if a client association succeeds. WARNING: DO NOT enable it in normal use. It may impair switch performance! Only recommended for debugging network issues.

trpzClientAuthenticationSuccessTrap.name: trpzClientAuthenticationSuccessTrap
trpzClientAuthenticationSuccessTrap.description: This trap is sent if a client authentication succeeds.

trpzClientDeAuthenticationTrap.name: trpzClientDeAuthenticationTrap
trpzClientDeAuthenticationTrap.description: This trap is sent if a client de-authentication occurred. Obsoleted by trpzClientDeAuthenticationTrap2.

trpzRFDetectBlacklistedTrap.name: trpzRFDetectBlacklistedTrap
trpzRFDetectBlacklistedTrap.description: This trap is sent if an association, re-association or de-association request (packet) is detected from a blacklisted transmitter (identified by MAC: 'trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr'). If 'trpzBlacklistingCause' is 'configured', then 'trpzBlacklistingRemainingTime' will be zero, meaning indefinite time (depending on administrative actions on the Black List). Otherwise, 'trpzBlacklistingRemainingTime' will indicate the time in seconds until this transmitter's requests could be allowed.

trpzRFDetectClientViaRogueWiredAPTrap2.name: trpzRFDetectClientViaRogueWiredAPTrap2
trpzRFDetectClientViaRogueWiredAPTrap2.description: This trap is sent when a client is detected that connected via a rogue AP that is attached to a wired port. trpzSourceWsIp is the IP address of the AC (switch) with the wired port. trpzPortNum is the port on the AC. trpzClientVLANid is the VLAN ID of the client's traffic. trpzClientVLANtag is the VLAN tag of the client's traffic. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the MAC address of the client. trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. trpzRFDetectRogueAPMacAddr is the MAC address of the Rogue AP (wired) the client is connected to. Obsoleted by trpzRFDetectClientViaRogueWiredAPTrap3.

trpzRFDetectAdhocUserDisappearTrap.name: trpzRFDetectAdhocUserDisappearTrap
trpzRFDetectAdhocUserDisappearTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection sweep finds that an ad-hoc user disappeared. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the MAC address of the ad-hoc user.

trpzApRejectLicenseExceededTrap.name: trpzApRejectLicenseExceededTrap
trpzApRejectLicenseExceededTrap.description: This trap is sent when an AC (wireless switch) receives a packet from an inactive AP and attaching that AP would make the AC exceed the maximum (licensed) number of active APs.

trpzClientDynAuthorChangeSuccessTrap.name: trpzClientDynAuthorChangeSuccessTrap
trpzClientDynAuthorChangeSuccessTrap.description: This trap is sent when the authorization attributes for a user are dynamically changed by an authorized dynamic authorization client. Obsoleted by trpzClientDynAuthorChangeSuccessTrap2.

trpzClientDynAuthorChangeFailureTrap.name: trpzClientDynAuthorChangeFailureTrap
trpzClientDynAuthorChangeFailureTrap.description: This trap is sent if a change of authorization request sent by an authorized dynamic authorization client is unsuccessful.

trpzClientDisconnectTrap.name: trpzClientDisconnectTrap
trpzClientDisconnectTrap.description: This trap is sent when a client session is terminated administratively. Obsoleted by trpzClientDisconnectTrap2.

trpzMobilityDomainFailOverTrap.name: trpzMobilityDomainFailOverTrap
trpzMobilityDomainFailOverTrap.description: This trap is sent when the Mobility Domain fails over to the secondary seed.

trpzMobilityDomainFailBackTrap.name: trpzMobilityDomainFailBackTrap
trpzMobilityDomainFailBackTrap.description: This trap is sent when the Mobility Domain fails back to the primary seed.

trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap.name: trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap
trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection finds a rogue device. XmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. ListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. ClassificationReason indicates the reason why the device is classified as rogue. Obsoleted by trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap2.

trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceDisappearTrap.name: trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceDisappearTrap
trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceDisappearTrap.description: This trap is sent when a rogue device has disappeared. This trap obsoletes the trpzRFDetectRogueDisappearTrap.

trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceTrap.name: trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceTrap
trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection finds a suspect device. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. ClassificationReason indicates the reason why the device is classified as suspect. Obsoleted by trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceTrap2.

trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceDisappearTrap.name: trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceDisappearTrap
trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceDisappearTrap.description: This trap is sent when a suspect device has disappeared. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. This trap obsoletes the trpzRFDetectInterferingRogueDisappearTrap.

trpzRFDetectClientViaRogueWiredAPTrap3.name: trpzRFDetectClientViaRogueWiredAPTrap3
trpzRFDetectClientViaRogueWiredAPTrap3.description: This trap is sent when a client is detected that connected via a rogue AP that is attached to a wired port. trpzSourceWsIp is the IP address of the AC (switch) with the wired port. trpzPortNum is the port on the AC. trpzClientVLANid is the VLAN ID of the client's traffic. trpzClientVLANtag is the VLAN tag of the client's traffic. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the MAC address of the client. trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. trpzRFDetectRogueAPMacAddr is the MAC address of the Rogue AP (wired) the client is connected to. ClassificationReason indicates the reason why the AP is classified as rogue. This trap obsoletes the trpzRFDetectClientViaRogueWiredAPTrap and trpzRFDetectClientViaRogueWiredAPTrap2.

trpzRFDetectClassificationChangeTrap.name: trpzRFDetectClassificationChangeTrap
trpzRFDetectClassificationChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent when RF detection classification rules change.

trpzConfigurationSavedTrap.name: trpzConfigurationSavedTrap
trpzConfigurationSavedTrap.description: This trap is sent when the running configuration of the switch is written to a configuration file.

trpzApNonOperStatusTrap2.name: trpzApNonOperStatusTrap2
trpzApNonOperStatusTrap2.description: This trap is sent when the AP changes state and the new one is a non-operational state. Obsoletes trpzApNonOperStatusTrap.

trpzApOperRadioStatusTrap2.name: trpzApOperRadioStatusTrap2
trpzApOperRadioStatusTrap2.description: This trap is sent when the Radio changes state. It also contains aggregate information about the AP in operational state - security level and service availability. Obsoleted by trpzApOperRadioStatusTrap3.

trpzMichaelMICFailure.name: trpzMichaelMICFailure
trpzMichaelMICFailure.description: Two Michael MIC failures were seen within 60 seconds of each other. Object trpzClientMACAddress indicates the source of the first failure, and object trpzClientMACAddress2 indicates the source of the second failure. Service is interrupted for 60 seconds on the radio due to TKIP countermeasures having commenced. The radio is identified by trpzApNum and trpzAPRadioNum. An alternative way to identify the radio is trpzRadioMACAddress. Obsoletes trpzMpMichaelMICFailure and trpzMpMichaelMICFailure2.

trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap3.name: trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap3
trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap3.description: This trap is sent when a client authorizes. If trpzClientAccessMode = 'ap': trpzApNum, trpzAPRadioNum, trpzRadioSSID identify the AP/radio/BSS providing wireless service to this client at the time this trap was sent. If trpzClientAccessMode = 'wired': trpzPhysPortNum identifies the physical port on the AC used by this wired-auth client. Obsoleted by trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap5.

trpzApManagerChangeTrap.name: trpzApManagerChangeTrap
trpzApManagerChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent when the AP's secondary link becomes its primary link.

trpzClientClearedTrap2.name: trpzClientClearedTrap2
trpzClientClearedTrap2.description: This trap is sent when a client session is cleared. Obsoleted by trpzClientClearedTrap3.

trpzMobilityDomainResiliencyStatusTrap.name: trpzMobilityDomainResiliencyStatusTrap
trpzMobilityDomainResiliencyStatusTrap.description: This trap is sent by a mobility domain seed to announce changes in resilient capacity status.

trpzApOperRadioStatusTrap3.name: trpzApOperRadioStatusTrap3
trpzApOperRadioStatusTrap3.description: This trap is sent when the Radio changes state. It also contains aggregate information about the AP in operational state - security level and service availability. Obsoletes trpzApOperRadioStatusTrap and trpzApOperRadioStatusTrap2.

trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap4.name: trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap4
trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap4.description: This trap is sent when a client authorizes. If trpzClientAccessMode = 'ap': trpzApNum, trpzAPRadioNum, trpzRadioSSID identify the AP/radio/BSS providing wireless service to this client at the time this trap was sent; trpzClientRadioType gives the type of radio used by this client. If trpzClientAccessMode = 'wired': trpzPhysPortNum identifies the physical port on the AC used by this wired-auth client. Obsoleted by trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap5.

trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap2.name: trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap2
trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap2.description: This trap is sent when RF detection finds a rogue device. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. trpzRFDetectXmtrRadioType indicates the Type of Radio used by the transmitter (rogue device). trpzRFDetectXmtrCryptoType indicates the Type of Crypto used by the transmitter (rogue device). trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. trpzRFDetectClassificationReason indicates the reason why the device is classified as rogue. Obsoletes trpzRFDetectRogueAPTrap, trpzRFDetectUnAuthorizedAPTrap, trpzRFDetectRogueDeviceTrap.

trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceTrap2.name: trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceTrap2
trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceTrap2.description: This trap is sent when RF detection finds a suspect device. trpzRFDetectXmtrMacAddr is the radio MAC address from the beacon. trpzRFDetectXmtrRadioType indicates the Type of Radio used by the transmitter (suspect device). trpzRFDetectXmtrCryptoType indicates the Type of Crypto used by the transmitter (suspect device). trpzRFDetectListenerListInfo is a display string of a list of listener information. trpzRFDetectClassificationReason indicates the reason why the device is classified as suspect. Obsoletes trpzRFDetectInterferingRogueAPTrap, trpzRFDetectSuspectDeviceTrap.

trpzClusterFailureTrap.name: trpzClusterFailureTrap
trpzClusterFailureTrap.description: This trap is sent when the cluster configuration failed to apply. If trpzClusterFailureReason = 'validation-error': The validation error is reported by the receiving end of the configuration updates. The receiving end can be any AC (switch) in the mobility domain: member, secondary seed or primary seed. - Primary seed will be the receiving end of configuration updates when Primary seed is joining the cluster and Secondary seed has preempt mode enabled. - Both Secondary seed and member will be at the receiving end when Primary seed is active.

trpzMultimediaCallFailureTrap.name: trpzMultimediaCallFailureTrap
trpzMultimediaCallFailureTrap.description: This trap is sent when a multimedia call fails.

trpzApTunnelLimitExceededTrap.name: trpzApTunnelLimitExceededTrap
trpzApTunnelLimitExceededTrap.description: This trap is sent by the AP primary controller (PAM) when an AP rejects a tunnel creation request because it has already created the maximum number of tunnels it can support.

trpzWsTunnelLimitExceededTrap.name: trpzWsTunnelLimitExceededTrap
trpzWsTunnelLimitExceededTrap.description: This trap is sent when the AC (wireless switch) rejects a tunnel creation request because it has reached the maximum number of tunnels supported (indicated by 'trpzWsTunnelLimit'). When trpzWsTunnelLimitType = 'platform-tunnel-limit' (2) the AC has reached the maximum tunnel capacity, which depends on the platform. When trpzWsTunnelLimitType = 'ap-ws-tunnel-limit' (3) the AC has reached the AP-to-switch tunnels limit, which depends on the current situation of the AC (mobility domain, network domain, network resiliency status).

trpzRFNoiseSourceTrap.name: trpzRFNoiseSourceTrap
trpzRFNoiseSourceTrap.description: This trap is sent upon the appearance of a new noise source. 'trpzRadioMACAddress' indicates the listener (the AP radio reporting the noise). A given combination of noise source ID, listener and channel should trigger this trap at most once every 15 minutes.

trpzM2UConvNotPossibleTrap.name: trpzM2UConvNotPossibleTrap
trpzM2UConvNotPossibleTrap.description: This trap is sent when multicast to unicast conversion is enabled on the AP, but cannot be performed.

trpzM2UConvAvailabilityRestoredTrap.name: trpzM2UConvAvailabilityRestoredTrap
trpzM2UConvAvailabilityRestoredTrap.description: This trap is sent when the multicast to unicast conversion can be resumed on the AP, after disruption.

trpzAutoTuneSuccessTrap.name: trpzAutoTuneSuccessTrap
trpzAutoTuneSuccessTrap.description: This trap is sent when an auto-tune operation completed successfully.

trpzAutoTuneFailureTrap.name: trpzAutoTuneFailureTrap
trpzAutoTuneFailureTrap.description: This trap is sent when an auto-tune operation failed to complete.

trpzClientDeAssociationTrap2.name: trpzClientDeAssociationTrap2
trpzClientDeAssociationTrap2.description: This trap is sent if a client de-association occurred. If trpzClientAccessMode = 'ap': trpzApNum, trpzApRadioIndex, trpzRadioSSID identify the AP/radio/BSS providing wireless service to this client before deassociation; If trpzClientAccessMode = 'wired': trpzPhysPortNum identifies the physical port on the AC used by this wired-auth client. Obsoletes trpzClientDeAssociationTrap.

trpzClientRoamingTrap2.name: trpzClientRoamingTrap2
trpzClientRoamingTrap2.description: This trap is sent if a client roams from one location to another. If trpzClientAccessMode = 'ap': trpzApNum, trpzApRadioIndex, trpzRadioSSID identify the AP/radio/BSS providing wireless service to this client, after roam; If trpzClientAccessMode = 'wired': trpzPhysPortNum identifies the physical port on the AC used by this wired-auth client, after roam. Obsoletes trpzClientRoamingTrap.

trpzClientIpAddrChangeTrap2.name: trpzClientIpAddrChangeTrap2
trpzClientIpAddrChangeTrap2.description: This trap is sent when an IP address of a client changes. The most likely cases for this are when the client first connects to the network and when a new IPv6 global address is assigned to the client. The pair of objects trpzClientIpAddrType/trpzClientIpAddr indicates the type and the value of the new IP address. If trpzClientAccessMode = 'ap': trpzApNum, trpzApRadioIndex, trpzRadioSSID identify the AP/radio/BSS providing wireless service to this client at the time this trap was sent; If trpzClientAccessMode = 'wired': trpzPhysPortNum identifies the physical port on the AC used by this wired-auth client. Obsoletes trpzClientIpAddrChangeTrap.

trpzClientDeAuthenticationTrap2.name: trpzClientDeAuthenticationTrap2
trpzClientDeAuthenticationTrap2.description: This trap is sent if a client de-authentication occurred. If trpzClientAccessMode = 'ap': trpzApNum, trpzApRadioIndex, trpzRadioSSID identify the AP/radio/BSS providing wireless service to this client at the time this trap was sent; If trpzClientAccessMode = 'wired': trpzPhysPortNum identifies the physical port on the AC used by this wired-auth client. Obsoletes trpzClientDeAuthenticationTrap.

trpzClientDynAuthorChangeSuccessTrap2.name: trpzClientDynAuthorChangeSuccessTrap2
trpzClientDynAuthorChangeSuccessTrap2.description: This trap is sent when the authorization attributes for a user are dynamically changed by an authorized dynamic authorization client. If trpzClientAccessMode = 'ap': trpzApNum, trpzApRadioIndex, trpzRadioSSID identify the AP/radio/BSS providing wireless service to this client at the time this trap was sent; If trpzClientAccessMode = 'wired': trpzPhysPortNum identifies the physical port on the AC used by this wired-auth client. Obsoletes trpzClientDynAuthorChangeSuccessTrap.

trpzClientDisconnectTrap2.name: trpzClientDisconnectTrap2
trpzClientDisconnectTrap2.description: This trap is sent when a client session is terminated administratively. If trpzClientAccessMode = 'ap': trpzApNum, trpzApRadioIndex, trpzRadioSSID identify the AP/radio/BSS providing wireless service to this client at the time this trap was sent; If trpzClientAccessMode = 'wired': trpzPhysPortNum identifies the physical port on the AC used by this wired-auth client. trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap5.name: trpzClientAuthorizationSuccessTrap5

As of release 8.0, device detection is done only for wireless clients (trpzClientAccessMode = 'ap').
